It sounds like you have `chkSession` from the cfscript code and then need it available on the client-side. To do that you just need to output the js script with the variable output. 

	  sessionId: &#39;&lt;cfoutput&gt;#chkSession.id#&lt;/cfoutput&gt;&#39;

If the variable is not available where you need to output it then add `request.` when setting and outputting it to place it into the request scope which is available from all code on the CF server running in the same request.

